<HL> Business Brief -- Volkswagen AG: Air Bags Will Be Standard On Audi 200 Series Cars </HL>
<SO> </SO>
<IN> AUT </IN>
<TEXT>
   Audi of America Inc., Troy, Mich., said driver-side air bags will be standard equipment on its 200 series cars and will add $950 to the base price of those models. 

   The unit of Volkswagen AG of West Germany said the new price of the 200 sedan will be $33,405, and the new price of the most expensive car in the series, the 200 Quattro wagon, will be $38,805. 

   Audi will offer driver-side air bags on most of its 100 series cars as a $950 option. 
For the 100E Automatic model, a driver-side air bag is available only as part of a $1,600 option package. 

